column6: Definition
A planned process by which a material is intentionally given to an organism resulting in exposure of the organism to that substance.
Adminstering a vaccine to an organism with the intention of inducing immunity against antigen components of the vaccine.
Administering an infectious agent to an organism in order to test if and how an infection will occur.
Transferring a solid tissue (transplant) or bodily fluid (transfusion) to an organism.
The process in which a disease unfolds.
The process in which an infectious disease unfolds.
The process in which an allergic disease unfolds.
The process in which an autoimmune disease unfolds.
The process in which cancer unfolds

column2: exposure to substance without evidence for disease
column6: An unplanned process in which an organism comes into contact with a substance without evidence for a disease caused by that exposure.

column4: exposure to substance without evidence for disease
column6: A process in which an infectious agent is in or on the body of an organism without causing detectable disease .

column2: exposure with existing immune reactivity without evidence for disease
column4: exposure to substance without evidence for disease
column6: A process in which an organism is exposed to a material entity which is evident by a detectable immune reactivity against it.

column2: documented exposure without evidence for disease
column4: exposure to substance without evidence for disease
column6: A process in which an organism is exposed to a substance which is evident from that process having been observed or documented.

column2: environmental exposure to endemic/ubiquitous agent without evidence for disease
column4: exposure to substance without evidence for disease
column6: A process in which an organism's exposure to a material entity is assumed from that material being commonly present in the environment of the organism.
An organism's lifspan which does not include exposure to a substance of interest.
An organism's lifespan for which there is no available information on an exposure to a material entity of interest.
A planned process in which solid tissue is transferred to an organism
A planned process in which a bodily fluid is transferred into an organism

column2: occurrence of cancer associated with virus
column6: An occurrence of cancer where there is evidence for the presence of a cancer causing oncovirus in the tumor.
